{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4 provides a visual summary of the proposed model.",
    "After features extraction using ViT, a transformer model 24 was used as a tensor for time-series classification to maintain the relationships between the slices.",
    "Due to the self-attention mechanisms of transformer-based time series classifications, long-term dependencies between time steps (features of each slice) were captured more effectively.",
    "We then used feature embedding to map each token sequence to a meaningful numeric vector.",
    "Since we used ViT to map the slices of each MRI to a sequence of dimensional numerical features, this transformer did not need an embedding module."
  ]
}